obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6199)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6199&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Medical Termination of`
  line `Pregnancy Act, 1971.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-`
  line `10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st April, 1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 285, dated 19th February, 1972, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3 (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6200)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6200&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) guardian means a person having the care of the person of a minor or a ^1[mentally ill person];`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) Medical Board means the Medical Board constituted under sub-section (2C) of section 3 of the Act;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) mentally ill person means a person who is in need of treatment by reason of any mental`
  line `disorder other than mental retardation;]`
  line
  line `(c) minor means a person who, under the provisions of the Indian Majority Act, 1875 (9 of`
  line `1875), is to be deemed not to have attained his majority;`
  line
  line `(d)registered medical practitioner means a medical practitioner who possesses any recognised`
  line `medical qualification as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956`
  line `(102 of 1956), whose name has been entered in a State Medical Register and who has such experience`
  line `or training in gynaecology and obstetrics as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(e) termination of pregnancy means a procedure to terminate a pregnancy by using medical or`
  line `surgical methods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 64 of 2002, s. 2, for lunatic (w.e.f. 18-6-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-9-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 18-6-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6201)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `When pregnancies may be terminated by registered medical practitioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6201&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1)Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), a registered medical`
  line `practitioner shall not be guilty of any offence under that Code or under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, if any pregnancy is terminated by him in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), a pregnancy may be terminated by a registered`
  line `medical practitioner,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the length of the pregnancy does not exceed twenty weeks, if such medical practitioner`
  line `is, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the length of the pregnancy exceeds twenty weeks but does not exceed twenty-four`
  line `weeks in case of such category of woman as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act, if not`
  line `less than two registered medical practitioners are,`
  line
  line `of the opinion, formed in good faith, that--`
  line
  line `(i) the continuance of the pregnancy would involve a risk to the life of the pregnant woman or of`
  line `grave injury to her physical or mental health; or`
  line
  line `(ii) there is a substantial risk that if the child were born, it would suffer from any serious physical`
  line `or mental abnormality.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of clause (a), where any pregnancy occurs as a result of failure`
  line `of any device or method used by any woman or her partner for the purpose of limiting the number of`
  line `children or preventing pregnancy, the anguish caused by such pregnancy may be presumed to`
  line `constitute a grave injury to the mental health of the pregnant woman.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b), where any pregnancy is alleged by the`
  line `pregnant woman to have been caused by rape, the anguish caused by the pregnancy shall be presumed`
  line `to constitute a grave injury to the mental health of the pregnant woman.`
  line
  line `(2A) The norms for the registered medical practitioner whose opinion is required for termination`
  line `of pregnancy at different gestational age shall be such as may be prescribed by rules made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2B) The provisions of sub-section (2) relating to the length of the pregnancy shall not apply to`
  line `the termination of pregnancy by the medical practitioner where such termination is necessitated by`
  line `the diagnosis of any of the substantial foetal abnormalities diagnosed by a Medical Board.`
  line
  line `(2C) Every State Government or Union territory, as the case may be, shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute a Board to be called a Medical Board for the purposes of this Act to`
  line `exercise such powers and functions as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2D) The Medical Board shall consist of the following, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) a Gynaecologist;`
  line
  line `(b) a Paediatrician;`
  line
  line `(c) a Radiologist or Sonologist; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other number of members as may be notified in the Official Gazette by the State`
  line `Government or Union territory, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) In determining whether the continuance of a pregnancy would involve such risk of injury to the health as is mentioned in sub-section (2), account may be taken of the pregnant womans actual or reasonably foreseeable environment.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) No pregnancy of a woman, who has not attained the age of eighteen years, or, who having attained the age of eighteen years, is a ^2[mentally ill person], shall be terminated except with the consent in writing of her guardian.`
  line
  line `(b) Save as otherwise provided in clause (a), no pregnancy shall be terminated except with the consent of the pregnant woman.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2021, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 24-9-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 64 of 2002, s. 3, for “lunatic” (w.e.f. 18-6-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6202)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Place where pregnancy may be terminated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 18-6-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6202&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Place where pregnancy may be terminated.--No termination of pregnancy shall be made in`
  line `accordance with this Act at any place other than--`
  line
  line `(a) a hospital established or maintained by Government, or`
  line
  line `(b) a place for the time being approved for the purpose of this Act by Government or a District`
  line `Level Committee constituted by that Government with the Chief Medical Officer or District Health`
  line `Officer as the Chairperson of the said Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the District Level Committee shall consist of not less than three and not more than five`
  line `members including the Chairperson, as the Government may specify from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6203)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Sections 3 and 4 when not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 64 of 2002, s. 5, for sub-section (2) and the Explanation (w.e.f. 18-6-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6203&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of section 4, and so much of the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3 as relate to the length of the pregnancy and the opinion of not`
  line `less than two registered medical practitioners, shall not apply to the termination of a pregnancy by a`
  line `registered medical practitioner in a case where he is of opinion, formed in good faith, that the termination`
  line `of such pregnancy is immediately necessary to save the life of the pregnant woman.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the termination of`
  line `pregnancy by a person who is not a registered medical practitioner shall be an offence punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years but which may extend to seven`
  line `years under that Code, and that Code shall, to this extent, stand modified.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever terminates any pregnancy in a place other than that mentioned in section 4, shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years but which may`
  line `extend to seven years.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person being owner of a place which is not approved under clause (b) of section 4 shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years but which may`
  line `extend to seven years.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, the expression owner in relation to a place means`
  line `any person who is the administrative head or otherwise responsible for the working or maintenance of a`
  line `hospital or place, by whatever name called, where the pregnancy may be terminated under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of this section, so much of the provisions of clause (d) of section 2`
  line `as relate to the possession, by registered medical practitioner, of experience or training in gynaecology`
  line `and obstetrics shall not apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (57693)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Protection of privacy of a woman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 8 of 2021, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=57693&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Protection of privacy of a woman.--(1) No registered medical practitioner shall reveal the`
  line `name and other particulars of a woman whose pregnancy has been terminated under this Act except to a`
  line `person authorised by any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6204)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 8 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6204&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the experience or training, or both, which a registered medical practitioner shall have if he`
  line `intends to terminate any pregnancy under this Act; and`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the category of woman under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ab) the norms for the registered medical practitioner whose opinion is required for termination of`
  line `pregnancy at different gestational age under sub-section (2A) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ac) the powers and functions of the Medical Board under sub-section (2C) of section 3.]`
  line
  line `(b) such other matters as are required to be or may be, provided by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in`
  line `which it is so laid or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in`
  line `the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6205)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6205&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by regulations,--`
  line
  line `(a) require any such opinion as is referred to in sub-section (2) of section 3 to be certified by a`
  line `registered medical practitioner or practitioners concerned, in such form and at such time as may be`
  line `specified in such regulations, and the preservation or disposal of such certificates;`
  line
  line `(b) require any registered medical practitioner, who terminates a pregnancy, to give intimation of`
  line `such termination and such other information relating to the termination as may be specified in such`
  line regulations;
  line
  line `(c) prohibit the disclosure, except to such persons and for such purposes as may be specified in`
  line `such regulations, of intimations given or information furnished in pursuance of such regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The intimation given and the information furnished in pursuance of regulations made by virtue of`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall be given or furnished, as the case may be, to the Chief Medical Officer`
  line `of the State.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) Every regulation made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who wilfully contravenes or wilfully fails to comply with the requirements of any`
  line `regulation made under sub-section (1) shall be liable to be punished with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6206)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428&sectionId=6206&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00006_197134_1517807320428
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any`
  line `registered medical practitioner for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
